What would I do if I were a bad actor, knowing Trump is likely to win? How could I undermine his effectiveness and superior governance or limit the positive impact he will achieve? 

I would focus on distracting his movement and creating fractures within it....

Silence Is Consent

I’m not new to this movement. I’ve been here since the beginning. The way I found Q, on its second post, was nothing short of a miracle. But let me tell you, this isn’t new to me. I’ve watched this movement grow, and I’ve watched it get shredded to pieces. And if we’re being honest, there’s a reason for that—a reason we need to face.

We didn’t take heed of what Q was really trying to tell us.

Was Q a psyop? Of course, it was. Disinformation and misinformation are necessary in an information war. Q even told us as much. But here’s the thing: while misinformation might be used to confuse the enemy, we—the people—aren’t supposed to spread false narratives, half-truths, or unchecked rumors. Our job is to dig, verify, and expel one thing ruthlessly: facts and truth.

The Weapons of Information War

The only weapon we have in this type of warfare is the truth. And we’re supposed to wield it mercilessly. That’s the entire point. Yet somewhere along the way, we lost that focus. We allowed bad actors, grifters, and chaos agents to twist this movement into something it was never supposed to be.

I’m not very well accepted in the Q community. In fact, I keep my connections small, and I’m okay with that. Most of the time, I prefer it that way. Most times I step into a space or a chat, conflict seems to follow me, and I don’t even have to say a word.

author/description: How could we be going through a Great Awakening if everybody’s retarded?™️
text:
Here’s one that’ll sting for some:

A lot of Trump and Q supporters aren’t actually “Trusting the Plan” anymore—they’re just too spineless to admit it. Why? Fear. Fear of being booted from their echo chambers. Fear of losing their little cult-approved camaraderie. Or maybe they’re just stuck between bad and worse—like choosing between shit and diarrhea. Spoiler alert: neither is appetizing, and if those are the options on the table, you better believe that’s by design.

Let’s face it—it’s a sad state of affairs when the “freedom movement” is made up of people too scared to voice their concerns. You know who else isn’t allowed to question leadership? Cult members. Halloooo 👋 

Here’s the reality: I’ve been dragged through the mud by the same cowards who preach about freedom but can’t handle an ounce of dissent. 
I say screw ‘em. 
Do what feels right for YOU. 
At the end of the day, you’re the one staring back at yourself in the mirror—not them. They never gave a damn about you anyway. All they wanted was the comfort of someone else validating their delusions and grifte. 

Stop being a pawn in their cowardly game. If this is about freedom, then act like it. Forget the backlash, do what’s right, and stand your ground—even if you’re alone. 
Fitting in with the mob isn’t freedom; it’s enslavement disguised as solidarity. 

Freedom means owning your voice, your choices, and your values—even when they put you at odds with the majority. 
It’s about standing firm when everyone else caves, because the moment you prioritize acceptance over truth, you forfeit your claim to liberty.

#EscanorMadeMeDoIt
